<exercise checkit-seed="0005" checkit-slug="DL4" checkit-title="Using Laplace Transforms to Solve IVPs">
  <statement>
      <p>
          Explain how to solve the following IVP.
      </p>
      <me>
          3 \, {y'} + 18 \, {y} - 3 \, {y''} = -15 \, \delta\left(t - 3\right);\qquad
          y(0)=0,
          y'(0)=-20
      </me>
      <p>Hint: <m>\frac{1}{x^{2} - x - 6} = -\frac{1}{5 \, {\left(x + 2\right)}} + \frac{1}{5 \, {\left(x - 3\right)}}</m>.</p>
  </statement>
  <answer>
      <me>
          \mathcal{L}\{y\}=\frac{5 \, e^{\left(-3 \, s\right)}}{s^{2} - s - 6} - \frac{20}{s^{2} - s - 6}
      </me>
      <me>
          {y} = e^{\left(3 \, t - 9\right)} \mathrm{u}\left(t - 3\right) - e^{\left(-2 \, t + 6\right)} \mathrm{u}\left(t - 3\right) - 4 \, e^{\left(3 \, t\right)} + 4 \, e^{\left(-2 \, t\right)}
      </me>
  </answer>
</exercise>
